# Cron configuration for daily stock update
# 
# To install this cron job:
# 1. Copy this file to your EC2 instance
# 2. Set timezone (if needed): sudo timedatectl set-timezone America/New_York
# 3. Run: crontab -e
# 4. Add the line below (adjust path and time as needed)
#
# Schedule: Weekdays at 4:30 PM (16:30) - adjust timezone as needed
# 
# 30 16 * * 1-5 cd ~/tradingAssistant && /usr/bin/python3 run_daily_jobs.py >> logs/cron.log 2>&1
#
# Alternative schedules:
# - Weekdays at 4:30 PM: 30 16 * * 1-5
# - Weekdays at 2:00 AM: 0 2 * * 1-5
# - Weekdays at 6:00 AM: 0 6 * * 1-5
# - Every weekday at noon: 0 12 * * 1-5
#
# To view cron logs:
# tail -f ~/tradingAssistant/logs/cron.log
#
# Note: Cron uses the system timezone. To run at 4:30 PM Eastern Time,
# set your EC2 instance timezone to America/New_York

# Recommended cron entry (uncomment and adjust):
# 30 16 * * 1-5 cd ~/tradingAssistant && /usr/bin/python3 run_daily_jobs.py >> logs/cron.log 2>&1

